geneVariantDescriptions.description: MEF2D-DAZAP1 results from the fusion of MEF2D and DAZAP1, which leads to increased transcriptional activation as demonstrated by a reporter assay in culture (PMID: 15744350, PMID: 27428428), and therefore, is predicted to result in a gain of protein function. MEF2D-DAZAP1 has been identified in B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia (PMID: 27428428).

references.title: Cloning and functional characterization of MEF2D/DAZAP1 and DAZAP1/MEF2D fusion proteins created by a variant t(1;19)(q23;p13.3) in acute lymphoblastic leukemia.
Genomic Profiling of Adult and Pediatric B-cell Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia.
